==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eel
<hw>Eel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets><?/l</ets>; akin
to D., G., & Dan. <ets>aal</ets>, Icel. <ets>⟦amac⟧ll</ets>, Sw.
<ets>⟦aring⟧l</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld> <def>An elongated
fish of many genera and species. The common eels of Europe and America
belong to the genus <gen>Anguilla</gen>. The electrical eel is a species
of <gen>Gymnotus</gen>. The so called <stype>vinegar eel</stype> is a
minute nematode worm. See <er>Conger eel</er>, <er>Electric eel</er>,
and <er>Gymnotus</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

